{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Interface Step 2: Define Test Scenarios",
  "description": "Step 2: Launch the modern GUI tool to help functional consultants define test scenarios in the Projects folder structure",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Launch the test scenario builder GUI by running: python ReusableTools/test_scenario_builder_modern.py\n\nUse controlPwshProcess with action='start' to launch it as a background process so it doesn't block. Then explain to the user:\n\n1. The modern GUI has opened in a new window\n2. Select the interface type (Inbound/Outbound/Approval) from the welcome screen\n3. All 3 predefined scenarios will auto-load based on selection\n4. Fill in interface details in the left sidebar\n5. Edit pre-loaded scenarios as needed:\n   - For upload steps: Use the Browse button (📁) to select test data files from Projects/{ClientName}/TestScripts/test_data/\n   - The test_data_file field will be saved in the JSON for Step 2 execution\n6. Click 'Save Test Scenarios' to save JSON file to Projects/{ClientName}/TestScripts/{interface_type}/\n7. After saving, click 'Step 3: Execute Tests in FSM' hook to continue"
  }
}